td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave the group for better exp?</span><hr size=1> 1) I'll leave a group for a friend<br>
2) I will leave a group because they are cluster F#%@s<br>
3) I will leave a group if I am currently waiting to get in another group but I make it clear that I'm waiting for the other group with I join them<br>
<br>
I will not leave a group to goto another group because they are not optimal.  I'd rather stay and make new friends with slightly less xp.  Often I group with friends and get less xp than I do solo.  I can still make 1 blue bubble a hour at 52 with absolutely ZERO risk though it is SOOOOO boring to play alone.<br>
<br>
Tizla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 8:10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23636.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave the group for better exp?</span><hr size=1> It's kind of a list thing on some servers.  You get into a crappier group downstairs where pulls are hard to get but you're doing something, and you toss your name in the hat for the more desired kobold/ledge camps.  As long as you're up front with the group you join downstairs that you're waiting on a spot somewhere else, its not too big of a deal from my experience.<br>
<br>
But then again, reputation &gt; xp anyday, so if you're very reputation-conscious, well, you might not want to &quot;abandon&quot; a lesser group especially if friends/guildies are in it.<br>
<br>
 <p>Seke Darktower<BR>
<a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=136737">Assassin of Unconquered</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukiradureatani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiradure Atani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 8:29:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23636.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Leave the group?</span><hr size=1> Personally, unless hell freezes over or there is some other never before encountered circumstance, I will never leave a group with friends for one with better experience or drops.  I'll even drop my soloing or whatever to go end up with friends.<br>
<br>
Hell, it makes sense to me.  For starters, you'll have more fun, and interact more. Secondly, you'll probably do better since they are your friends and usually hunting buddies.  Those you've grouped with your whole life do very good with you, you'll probably do better if things get rough with your friends because you know how they react. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukiradureatani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiradure Atani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 8:30:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23636.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Leave the group?</span><hr size=1> -=(Edit:  Double Post)=- <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukiradureatani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiradure Atani</A> at: 5/7/02 8:37:26 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualitaryoko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlitaRyoko</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.co.jp/HeartLand-Sumire/7069/img/ddani.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 9:05:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23636.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.buzzdc.com/buzzdc/mssg_brd/avatar.php?userid=699&dateline=1017353622 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave the group?</span><hr size=1> For me it's not about the experience nor the loot when groupin, but rather the communications and the cohesiveness of the work.  Sometimes a group just doesn't work, other times everything works out perfectly.  Also depends on the nature of the persons withing the group, sometimes players can be outright rude.  And personally I don't want to be in a group that is putting down other members of the group.     <p><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=174301><img src=http://files.bloodtide.org/pics/sig-majalita.jpg></p></A>
Majalita Darkhour
Mistress of The Fibbynux
Magician 
Sacrificial Lamb</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 9:16:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23636.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave the group?</span><hr size=1> I'll leave a group when:<br>
<br>
1. A guild event is called;<br>
2. Friend needs help and my leaving will not cripple the group which is rarely the case: a rogue can be replaced by pretty much any melee (unless there are locked doors involved) though it might not be as optimal;<br>
3. The group sucks bigtime (sorry but my time is too precious to waste on unnecessary CRs and ridiculously slow exp).  This doesn't mean suboptimal groups but *sucky* groups;<br>
4. If I'm grouped with people at, say, Seb zone in waiting to get the right classes I'll leave if an opportunity to join a complete group comes up;<br>
5. When the zone becomes so crowded that the group which otherwise might've been good now sucks;<br>
6. I can't stand one or more of the other party members.<br>
<br>
I will NOT leave when:<br>
<br>
1. CR needs to be done.  Its surprising how many people mysteriously go LD when CR is necessary;<br>
2. Without giving the group an opportunity to find a replacement if possible;<br>
3. In the middle of a fight.  I'll at least fight up to zone in if a replacement can't get there;<br>
4. The group is suboptimal but bearable.<br>
<br>
Last night a bard decided he needed to go to a VS raid while we were at chef in Seb.  There were four mezzed mobs in the room and he quit and ran.  I would NEVER do that.  There is justice however and he died near gang so half an hour after he left he got a rez as our group was making its way back to zone in.  The cleric rezzed him where he died.  Personally I would've made him wait til we got to zone in (by dragging his corpse).  Of course he didn't stay to help fight up to zone in.<br>
